wiki.content:
Originally written and recorded by Leonard Cohen on his 1988 album, "I'm Your Man". Michael Bublé covered "I'm Your Man" in 2007 for his album "Call me irresponsible".

wiki.summary: Originally written and recorded by Leonard Cohen on his 1988 album, "I'm Your Man". Michael Bublé covered "I'm Your Man" in 2007 for his album "Call me irresponsible".

track.name: I'm Your Man
comments: this is a serenade to my ears <3
This song was born to be Jazz.
What a great voice Michael has!!!
I love how much passion there is in this song...just right <3
You can be my man any day of the week ;)
agree, this one is really great cover
Great cover, especially towards the last minute or so. Not a patch on the original though...
Where did this guy come from? His voice is wonderful and smooth. I like this one very much. Very romantic.
love his rendition of Leonard Cohen's I'm Your Man,.... well, love him too!
